Mar 25, 2025
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
S.B. 730
SESSION 2025
PRINCIPAL CLERK
S D
SENATE BILL DRS45294-RI-11
Short Title: Expand CEPS/Nuclear and Hydro. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Jarvis (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO EXPAND THE CLEAN ENERGY PORTFOLIO STANDARD TO INCLUDE
3 EXISTING NUCLEAR AND LARGE HYDROELECTRIC POWER FACILITIES.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 62-133.8 reads as rewritten:
6 "§ 62-133.8. Clean Energy and Energy Efficiency Portfolio Standard (CEPS).
7 (a) Definitions. – As used in this section:
8 …
9 (4c) "New clean energy facility" means:
10 a. A new renewable energy facility; or
11 b. Facilities placed into service on or after January 1, 2007, which that
12 are either (i) a nuclear energy facility, including an uprate to a nuclear
13 energy facility, or (ii) a fusion energy facility.
14 (5) "New renewable energy facility" means a renewable energy facility that
15 either:
16 a. Was placed into service on or after January 1, 2007.
17 b. Delivers or has delivered electric power to an electric power supplier
18 pursuant to a contract with NC GreenPower Corporation that was
19 entered into prior to January 1, 2007.
20 c. Is a hydroelectric power facility with a generation capacity of 10
21 megawatts or less that delivers electric power to an electric power
22 supplier.
23 …."
24 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law.
*DRS45294-RI-11*

